  "local_port": 43036,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are best places to visit in mangalore?",
  "response": "Mangalore, officially known as Mangaluru, is a vibrant port city in the Indian state of Karnataka. It offers a mix of natural beauty, cultural heritage, and religious landmarks. Here are some of the best places to visit in Mangalore:\n\n### 1. **Panambur Beach**\n   - A clean and scenic beach where you can relax, enjoy water sports, and watch the sunset. The beach also has facilities like camel rides and a children\u2019s play area.\n\n### 2. **Kudroli Sri Gokarnanatheshwara Temple**\n   - A beautiful temple dedicated to Lord Shiva, known for its vibrant architecture and religious significance. The temple is especially lively during festivals.\n\n### 3. **Pilikula Nisargadhama**\n   - A sprawling eco-tourism spot featuring a zoo, botanical garden, lake, and cultural center. It\u2019s a great place for nature lovers and families.\n\n### 4. **Sultan Battery**\n   - A historical watchtower built by Tipu Sultan, offering a glimpse into Mangalore's past and a serene view of the surrounding area.\n\n### 5. **Mangaladevi Temple**\n   - An ancient temple dedicated to Goddess Mangaladevi, from which the city derives its name. It\u2019s a peaceful and spiritually significant site.\n\n### 6. **St. Aloysius Chapel**\n   - A stunning chapel known for its intricate frescoes and paintings, resembling the Sistine Chapel in Vatican City.\n\n### 7. **Tannirbhavi Beach**\n   - A secluded beach accessible by ferry or road, offering a tranquil escape from the city\u2019s hustle and bustle.\n\n### 8. **Kadri Manjunath Temple**\n   - A historic temple dedicated to Lord Manjunath (Shiva), known for its bronze statue of Lord Lokeshwara and serene surroundings.\n\n### 9. **Ullal Beach**\n   - Another serene beach located near Mangalore, known for its pristine sands and tranquil atmosphere. It\u2019s less crowded than Panambur Beach.\n\n### 10. **Surathkal Beach**\n   - A picturesque beach with a lighthouse, perfect for watching sunsets and enjoying the coastal breeze.\n\n### 11. **Milagres Church**\n   - One of the oldest churches in Mangalore, known for its beautiful architecture and peaceful ambiance.\n\n### 12. **Shri Venkataramana Temple**\n   - A historic temple dedicated to Lord Venkataramana (Vishnu), known for its intricate carvings and spiritual ambiance.\n\n### 13. **Padua Beaches**\n   - A group of serene beaches near the Padua Church, offering a peaceful retreat for visitors.\n\n### 14. **Mangalore Port**\n   - One of the busiest ports in India, offering a glimpse into the city\u2019s maritime activity. You can also enjoy a boat ride here.\n\n### 15. **Attur Church (St. Lawrence Shrine)**\n   - A famous Roman Catholic church known for its annual feast and beautiful architecture.\n\nMangalore is also famous for its unique cuisine, so don\u2019t miss trying local delicacies like **Neer Dosa**, **Kori Rotti**, **Kundapura Koli Saaru**, and seafood dishes. The city\u2019s blend of culture, history, and natural beauty makes it a must-visit destination in Karnataka.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
